{
  "texts": [
    "Carrier mobility refers to how efficiently charge carriers move through the semiconductor material.",
    "The increased thermal energy enables carriers to move more freely, leading to enhanced electrical conductivity.",
    "However, this increased mobility can raise the likelihood of recombination events, particularly near the contacts, resulting in reduced overall efficiency (Jošt et al., 2020).",
    "Dark current, representing the current generated within a solar cell in the absence of light, tends to increase with temperature.",
    "This rise is primarily due to thermally generated carriers."
  ]
}